ding starts from the current position. I also want to test a scenario with a prefix, message, and suffix to verify this process. It could help improve the encoding features!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Testing header serialization**\\n\\nI’m thinking about testing all roundtrip header types, especially BYTE and SHORT. The existing factory handles getByte and getShort but doesn’t cover message serialization for these types. While there's already support for certain headers in messageRoundTrip, adding BYTE and SHORT would alter the existing logic, which I'm not permitted to do. So, I consider creating a new test, \\\"messageRoundTripPreservesByteAndShortHeaders,\\\" since it follows the same flow but introduces new header types without duplicating existing logic.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Testing message features**\\n\\nI’m working on testing the roundtrip flow by examining different types, possibly focusing on dynamic access classes. However, I realize that there might be some \\\"functional features\\\" not covered, like byte and short wire support. The logic flow seems similar, but could I also combine encodeHeaders with comprehensive header type coverage? I need to ensure that Message.encodeHeaders correctly serializes all header value types, including bytes and shorts, and maybe look into inspecting metadata report classes as well.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_sNlxW93E92G6ITs1CEJ5bMQ7|fc_016dc4f8cc0761dc0169f787f590008191a3696e19fa13d306", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "metadata/software.amazon.eventstream/eventstream/1.0.1/reachability-metadata.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5023, "output": 641, "cacheRead": 24576, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30240, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777829864938, "responseId": "resp_016dc4f8cc0761dc0169f787e964548191b01747c874